1. Compatibility: Without , cmake_minimum_required(....) 
               CMake doesn’t know which policies to apply, which can cause inconsistent behavior across different versions.
• 	Best practice: Always put this command at the very top of your CMakeLists.txt

2. cmake -S . -B out/build
   <!-- At this point, if we modify the code. No need to re-run cmake commands -->
   <!-- But if file deleted or added, need to RUN cmake command -->
   <!-- <OPTION 1> -->
   cd out/build
   make
   ./OLAS
   <!-- <OPTION 2> -->
   make -C out/build
   ./out/build/OLAS
